1.speaker: PANDA
1.character: 笹を食べながらのんびりするのは最高だなぁ
1.definition: Chilling and eating bamboo grass is the best thing ever.

2.speaker: PANDA MAMA
2.character: ちょっと  またこの子は昼間からゴロゴロして
2.definition: Hey now. Look at you, being so lazy so early in the day.

3.speaker: PANDA MAMA
3.character: 掃除の邪魔よ  どきなさい
3.definition: You're in the way of my cleaning. Scoot.

5.speaker: PANDA
5.character: お母さん  おかわり

6.speaker: PANDA MAMA
6.character: どうするの  あなた将来は
6.definition: Exactly what do you have planned for your future?

7.speaker: PANDA
7.character: もう  ゴロゴロしてるときに  将来の話なんかしないでよ
7.definition: Jeez... Could we not talk about my future when I'm relaxing?

8.speaker: PANDA MAMA
8.character: 暇があるなら  ちょっとはバイトでも探しなさい
8.definition: If you have so much time to relax, you could go look for a part-time job. I'm too busy relaxing, so I'll do it later. Don't try to suck me up!

10.speaker: PANDA
10.character: どうしてお母さんはゴロゴロする忙しさが分かんないんだろな
10.definition: I wonder why Mom can't understand how much time relaxing takes up.

11.speaker: PANDA
11.character: えーと  働かないでお金がもらえる仕事が載っているのはどれですか
11.definition: Excuse me, which of these will have jobs where I can get paid to do nothing?

12.speaker: CLERK
12.definition: I don't think there is one.

14.speaker: PANDA
14.character: どうせなら  お洒落なバイトがいいなぁ
14.definition: If I really have to work, I'd prefer a really fancy job.

17.speaker: PANDA
17.character: あ  もしもし  パンダと申しますが
17.definition: Oh, hi, my name is Panda.

18.speaker: PANDA
18.character: そちらでデザインなー  デザイナーのアルバイト募集してますよね
18.definition: You're advertising a part-time position for a designer, right?

19.speaker: PERSON
19.character: ええ  そうですよ  経験は？
19.definition: Yes, we are. Do you have experience?

21.speaker: PERSON
21.character: パソコンのマウスは使えますか
21.definition: Are you able to use a computer mouse?

22.speaker: PANDA
22.character: 使えないです  あんまり細かい作業はできません
22.definition: Not at all! I'm not very good with detailed work.

23.speaker: PERSON
23.character: そうですか  得意なことはありますか
23.definition: I see. Do you have anything you're good at?

25.speaker: PANDA
25.character: 笹を食べたり  寝ながらぼんやりするのが得意です
25.definition: I'm good at eating bamboo grass, and zoning out while lying down.

27.speaker: PANDA
27.character: もしもし  そちらでインテリアコーディネーターも募集してますよね
27.definition: Oh, hello? You're also advertising a position for an interior coordinator, right?

29.speaker: PANDA
29.character: インテリアコーディネーターって  なんですか
29.definition: What, exactly, is an interior coordinator?

30.speaker: PANDA MAMA
30.definition: There you are being lazy again.

31.speaker: PANDA MAMA
31.character: アルバイト見つかったの
31.definition: Did you find a part-time job?

33.speaker: PANDA MAMA
33.character: 確かコンビニで募集してたでしょう
33.definition: Weren't there openings at the convenience store?

34.speaker: PANDA
34.definition: The convenience store? They have too many things. I won't be able to remember them all! Don't try to suck me up!

35.speaker: PANDA
35.character: もう  外でだらだらしようっと
35.definition: Jeez. I think I'll wander around outside. Huh?  A string. Could you get it? Sure. Got it!

37.speaker: PANDA
37.definition: Stay right there. Hey, wait! Wow, I didn't know there was a café here. Hello.

38.speaker: POLAR BEAR
38.character: ようこそ  しろくまカフェへ

39.speaker: POLAR BEAR
39.character: お客様  お一人様ですか
39.definition: Table for one, sir? Oh, well, I'm not exactly a custo—

40.speaker: POLAR BEAR
40.definition: Please have a seat anywhere you like.

42.speaker: POLAR BEAR
42.definition: May I take your order? Let's see... Do you have bamboo?

43.speaker: POLAR BEAR
43.definition: We don't have any bamboo. Then could I get bamboo grass?

44.speaker: POLAR BEAR
44.definition: We don't have bamboo grass either. Then I'll have an iced coffee.

47.speaker: PENGUIN
47.character: 財布のポイントカードって増えすぎちゃわない
47.definition: Do you ever get too many point cards in your wallet?

48.speaker: POLAR BEAR
48.character: ペンギンさん  ポイント貯める派

49.speaker: PENGUIN
49.definition: Yep.  Oh, could I get another café mocha? Seconds {\i1}(okawari){\i0}. What?

51.speaker: PENGUIN
51.definition: That would be the daily special {\i1}(higawari){\i0}.

56.speaker: PENGUIN
56.character: このカフェ  ダジャレがなければなぁ
56.definition: You know, if it weren't for all the puns in this café...

57.speaker: PENGUIN
57.character: そういえば  アルバイト募集してるんだって
57.definition: By the way, I heard you were looking for a part-timer?

58.speaker: POLAR BEAR
58.character: うん  人手が足りなくて

59.speaker: POLAR BEAR
59.character: ペンギンさん  どう

60.speaker: PENGUIN
60.character: え？ぼく  お客とバイトの両立  できるかな
60.definition: Who, me? I wonder if I could handle being a customer and a part-timer.

61.speaker: POLAR BEAR
61.character: ウーソ  これから四名ほど  面接に来るんだよ
61.definition: Just kidding.  I have about four interviews lined up.

62.speaker: PENGUIN
62.character: なんだ  ちょっと考えちゃったよ
62.definition: Oh.  And here I was actually considering it.

63.speaker: PANDA
63.definition: Could I have an interview, too?

64.speaker: PANDA
64.character: 僕もアルバイトしたいと思って
64.definition: I was also thinking of working part-time.

66.speaker: PENGUIN
66.definition: What?! Well then, will the first applicant please come up.

69.speaker: POLAR BEAR
69.character: えーと  ホール係やれますか
69.definition: Let's see...  Would you be able to work the hall?

70.speaker: BADGER
70.character: はい  ホールなら任せてください
70.definition: Yes!  You can leave the holes to me!

71.speaker: BADGER
71.character: 穴を掘るの  得意なんです
71.definition: I'm a pro at digging holes!

72.speaker: PENGUIN
72.character: いや  そのホールは違うし

76.speaker: POLAR BEAR
76.character: 料理とか  運べますか
76.definition: Are you able to carry orders?

80.speaker: TORTOISE
80.definition: Please let me work about a hundred years.

81.speaker: POLAR BEAR
81.definition: Er, I don't think that'll be possible.

84.speaker: POLAR BEAR
84.definition: Not exactly what we're looking for.

86.speaker: ANTEATER
86.character: い  威嚇ができます

88.speaker: POLAR BEAR
88.definition: Will the last applicant step up, please.

92.speaker: PENGUIN
92.character: やっとまともな人が来たね

93.speaker: POLAR BEAR
93.character: パンダ君  何か得意なことはありますか
93.definition: Is there anything you're good at, Panda?

94.character: はい  ゴロゴロしながら笹を食べることです
94.definition: Yes! I'm very good at lying around and eating bamboo grass.

96.speaker: POLAR BEAR
96.character: えーと  条件に希望はありますか
96.definition: Er, let's see... Are there any specific conditions you'd like to request?

98.speaker: POLAR BEAR
98.character: うん  週二日ですか
98.definition: Hm, you'd prefer two days? Oh, you mean I could just work one day a week?

99.speaker: POLAR BEAR
99.character: いや  せめて週四日くらい
99.definition: No, no.  I was hoping for at least four days a week. I definitely can't do that.

100.speaker: PANDA
100.definition: Oh, but... if you pick me up, I'll come right away.

101.speaker: POLAR BEAR
101.character: 僕が呼びに行くんですか
101.definition: I have to come and get you? Oh, of course not.

102.speaker: PANDA
102.character: 遅刻した場合だけですよ

103.speaker: PENGUIN
103.definition: You have every intention of being late, don't you?

104.speaker: POLAR BEAR
104.character: ちなみに  やる気はありますか
104.definition: Just curious... do you really intend to work?

108.speaker: ALL
108.definition: What?! Are you really that surprised?

110.speaker: POLAR BEAR
110.definition: ...I wasn't able to find a part-timer. That's too bad. You're still here?!

111.speaker: PANDA
111.character: 家に帰ると  お母さんに吸われるし
111.definition: If I go home, my mom will try to suck me up.

114.speaker: GIRL
114.character: あのう　面接中すみません
114.definition: Pardon me, I hate to interrupt you during your interviews.

115.speaker: SLOTH
115.definition: I would like to live in...

117.speaker: GIRL
117.character: あのう  アルバイト希望じゃないみたいですよ
117.definition: I don't think he meant a live-in employee.

118.speaker: SLOTH
118.character: 庭に住み込みたいんですー
118.definition: I would like to live in your yard.

119.speaker: GIRL
119.character: ここまで運んで欲しいって　頼まれちゃいまして
119.definition: He asked me if I would bring him here.

120.speaker: POLAR BEAR
120.definition: What is your name, Miss? Who, me?  It's Sasako.

124.speaker: PANDA
124.character: 僕今日、すごくいい感じのカフェ見つけちゃったよ
124.definition: I found a really neat café today.

125.speaker: PANDA
125.character: しろくまカフェって言うんだけど

126.speaker: PANDA MAMA
126.character: なんに言ってるの？知ってるわよ
126.definition: What are you talking about? Of course I know about it.

128.speaker: PANDA MAMA
128.character: ずっと前からあるじゃない？
128.definition: It's been there for a really long time.
